            <scopecontent>
                <p>A small group of legal opinions of Horace Binney, Philadelphia attorney and
                    counsel to the United States Insurance Company. Most are in letter form,
                    addressed to Israel Pleasants, president of the company, and his successor,
                    Chandler Price, and deal with maritime insurance cases arising from the
                    operation of British Orders in council, Napoleon's Berlin and Milan Decrees, but
                    there are some cases dealing with the property rights of women.</p>
            </scopecontent>


